JOHN MACKMILL (Mackmiell),
200 acs., Low. Par, of Is. of Wight Co;
adj. Wm. Joyner; & Capt. Applewaite;
28 Oct. 1697, p. 104. ‘Trans, of 4 pers:
Maren Prater, John Colesell,, Wm.
Keay, Tho. Fisher.

SAME. 3087 A., 3 R., 24 P., Henrico Co; on N. side of James River;
same date & page. Beg. on S. side of
Chickahomony Sw., adj. Mr. Beachamp}
&c. Granted Mr. Thomas Cock, 4 Oct.
1675, deserted, & now granted by order,
&c. Imp. of 62 pers.*

RICHARD HOFFINTON, 67 acs.,
Accomack Co: bet. Pongotege & Nandwe Creeks; adj. Mr. Robert Hutchinson;
Peter Rogers; Michael Richards (or
Rickard) ; & Capt. George Nicol, Hack;
25 Apr. 1702, p. 446. Trans. of 2 pers:
Richard Wadkinson, Eliza. Kendrick.

ROBERT DAVIS & MARY, his wife,
one of the daughters of Ambrose Lipscomb, dec’d; 137 acs., King Wm. Co;
in Pamunkey Neck; in St. John’s Par;
adi. Martin Slaughter; Willaroy’s line;
John Lipscomb; & Wm. Lipscomb; 28
Oct. 1702, p. 490. Trans, of 3 pers:
Isaac Palmer, Thomas Brown, Mary
Fitzgerald.

JOHN POWELL, 313 acs., Low. Par.
of Isle of Wight Co; adj. Wm, Powell;
23 Oct. 1703, p. 574. Trans. of 7 pers.*

SAME. 3664 acs; same Co., & date;
p. 613. §S. side of James River, on both
sides the Road to the French settlement;
beg. upon water course of Powhite Cr;
to cor. of Mr. Thomas Jefferson &
partners; up water course of Lucey’s
‘Br; above the spring; to cor. of
Shamapoke; up water course of Pocoshock; &c. Trans. of 74 pers.* Note:
Same as second above.

MR. JOHN GRANGER, 72 acs.
Henrico Co; S. side of James River;
adj. Robert Fergrese; Mr. James Baugh;
Richard Womack; & Jno. Pickett; 20
Oct. 1704, p. 628. Trans, of 2 pers:
Gilbert Wetherly, William Huff.

ROBERT BOLLING, 50 acs., Hentico Co,, 2 May 1705, p. 646. Escheated
from John Cookney, dec'd., by inquisition under William Randolph, Gent.,
Esch’r., &c.

HANCOCK CUSTIS, 50 acs., N’ampton Co., 2 May 1705, p. 646. Escheated
from Emanuell Hall, dec’d., by inquisition under John Custis, Esqr., Esch’r.,
&ec,

MARY ASCOUGH, 633 acs., Henrico Co., 2 May 1705, p. 648. Escheated
from Henry Ascough, dec’d., by inquisition under Wm, Randolph, Gent.,
Esch’r,, &c,

SAME. 10344 acs; same Co., & date;
Pp. 723. Escheated from Thomas Lyddall,
dec’d., by inquisition under Isaac Allerton, Esch’r., 18 Aug. 1685, &c,
